1 cons ervation effort in American history - which constitute,
2 collectively, the American System of Conservation Funding.
3 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
4 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
5 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives recognizes America’s
6 anglers, boaters, the sportfishing industry, state fish and wildlife
7 agencies, and the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service for their leading
8 role in restoring healthy populations of fish and aquatic resources,
9 both game and non-game, to the abundance we see today with the help
10 of the Sport Fish Restoration Program, in this the 75th anniversary
11 year of the program’s establishment as part of the American System
12 of Conservation Funding.
13 THAT an official copy of this resolution be provided to the
14 Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission, all Oklahoma
15 Congressional offices, and local, regional, and national media
16 sources so that all may know and appreciate the foresight and
17 contributions from anglers, the sportfishing industry, state fish
18 and wildlife agencies, and the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service on
19 behalf of our nation’s fisheries and aquatic resources.
20
21 DIRECT TO CALENDAR.
